  <title>Cogl.Bitmap.new_from_buffer</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function new_from_buffer(buffer: <link xref="Cogl.Buffer">Cogl.Buffer</link>, format: <link xref="Cogl.PixelFormat">Cogl.PixelFormat</link>, width: Number(gint), height: Number(gint), rowstride: Number(gint), offset: Number(gint)): <link xref="Cogl.Bitmap">Cogl.Bitmap</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_bitmap_new_from_buffer()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Wraps some image data that has been uploaded into a <link xref="Cogl.Buffer"/> as
a <link xref="Cogl.Bitmap"/>. The data is not copied in this process.</p>
  <p>Since 1.8</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>buffer</code></title>
  <p>A <link xref="Cogl.Buffer"/> containing image data</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>format</code></title>
  <p>The <link xref="Cogl.PixelFormat"/> defining the format of the image data
         in the given <code>buffer</code>.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>width</code></title>
  <p>The width of the image data in the given <code>buffer</code>.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>height</code></title>
  <p>The height of the image data in the given <code>buffer</code>.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>rowstride</code></title>
  <p>The rowstride in bytes of the image data in the given <code>buffer</code>.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>offset</code></title>
  <p>The offset into the given <code>buffer</code> to the first pixel that
         should be considered part of the <link xref="Cogl.Bitmap"/>.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>a <link xref="Cogl.Bitmap"/> encapsulating the given <code>buffer</code>.</p>
</item>
